{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1aef8ca5-7a4b-451e-a608-847e84248f1a","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files must be listed in dependency order. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Domain.fs` is listed *after* `Services.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_WcTk38faTcaYRHgsXRbqgY","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8ae941809b1f4e1e86b6fa21fb635868/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8ae941809b1f4e1e86b6fa21fb635868/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"01e65b6c-42aa-4c8f-bccb-d6d3511528a9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files must be listed in dependency order — a file can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* it in the `.fsproj`.\n\nCurrently the `.fsproj` has:\n1. `Services.fs` (depends on `Domain.fs`)\n2. `Domain.fs` (defines types)\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on both)\n\n`Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` is listed after it. The fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":439,"requestId":"DBD4:27CF97:152F96D:17C569D:69FD3406"},"id":"076f09c3-227b-4738-8217-47861a0867c6","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:53:34.023Z","parentId":"957d36e9-adb8-484d-acc2-9ae61c207ddc"}
